BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:⭐ APPLY NOW: 2026-27 Student Media Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T000000
UID:fee742af812bf6199fcd331f61b17d4f@solutionsjournalism.org
DESCRIPTION:This opportunity is open to student newsrooms and journalism s
 chools based in the United States.\nIt’s time to apply if your student n
 ewsroom wants to be part of next year’sStudent Media Challenge– a coho
 rt of student news outlets at colleges and universities that will do solut
 ions reporting on the urgent topic of youth mental health over the 2026-27
  academic year. The Challenge comes with grant money to support reporting 
 and engagement work\, as well as two meetings each month: one with the ent
 ire cohort and me to share progress and benefit from training modules and 
 guest lectures\; and the other with me to troubleshoot and strategize abou
 t your own newsroom’s stories.Apply by March 20.\nJoin us for an info se
 ssion about the program.We're offering two:March 4andMarch 10. Both info s
 essions are at 1 p.m. Eastern Time and advance registration is required.
LOCATION:This opportunity is open to student newsrooms and journalism scho
 ols based in the United States.
URL:https://www.tfaforms.com/5213015
X-SOURCE:Solutions Journalism Network
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Society of Professional Journalists SkillsFest 26
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T000000
UID:28122a04923001e300c4811334a08a8b@solutionsjournalism.org
DESCRIPTION:Online\nSkillsFest 26 is a free\, two-day virtual program open
  to all. We might be a little biased\, but we’re especially excited abou
 t the session “Solutions Journalism: How to Engage Audiences and Increas
 e Impact by Rigorously Covering What’s Going Right\,” presented by SJN
 ’s Sharon Bloyd-Peshkin. In this session\, you’ll learn the ins and ou
 ts of solutions journalism and how this approach to in-depth reporting can
  invigorate your newsroom and enhance its impact.Register for the conferen
 ce here.
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://www.spj.org/skillsfest/
X-SOURCE:Solutions Journalism Network
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Earth Journalism Network's Biodiversity Media Grants
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000
UID:74161ff9c4bcee7cade439f73b85208a@solutionsjournalism.org
DESCRIPTION:The Earth Journalism Network has opened applications for itsBi
 odiversity Media Grants. Three or four newsrooms in low- to middle-income 
 countries (as defined by the World Bank) will receive grants of 10\,000 to
  12\,000 euros each “to increase understanding of the threats to biodive
 rsity and the solutions needed to address these challenges.” The deadlin
 e is March 28.
URL:https://earthjournalism.net/opportunities/biodiversity-media-grants-20
 26
X-SOURCE:Solutions Journalism Network
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2026 Covering Climate Now Journalism Awards
