BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monthly Introduction to Solutions Journalism Webinar: April
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T000000
UID:bed62a8bf875ae3f47605edb8243adbc@solutionsjournalism.org
DESCRIPTION:Online (Zoom)\nThis one-hour Solutions Journalism Network webi
 nar will explore the principles and pillars of solutions journalism. We wi
 ll discuss its importance\, outline key steps for reporting a solutions st
 ory\, and share tips and resources for journalists investigating responses
  to social problems. We will also introduce additional resources\, such as
  the Solutions Story Tracker\, a database with over 17\,000 stories tagged
  by beat\, publication\, author\, location and more\, along with a virtual
  heat map highlighting successful efforts worldwide.\nThis training will b
 e led by SJN's engagement director Allen Arthur and Juanita Ramos from the
  AP.
LOCATION:Online (Zoom)
URL:https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_5AxjHtpeRROOPY8qDZ16Hw
X-SOURCE:Solutions Journalism Network
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Rethinking Election Coverage: A Solutions Journalism Approach for 
 Student Media
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T000000
UID:71055e1b3f90d4907a7d645f41589003@solutionsjournalism.org
DESCRIPTION:Online\nElections deserve more than polls\, pundits and partis
 an framing. Join the Students Learn Students Vote (SLSV) Coalition and SJN
 ’s Jaisal Noor and Sharon Bloyd-Peshkin for a training on how to cover e
 lections through a solutions journalism lens. We’ll explore what’s wor
 king\, what students need to know\, and how journalism can help build trus
 t. This online workshop is designed specifically for student newsroom edit
 ors and reporters.
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://secure.everyaction.com/6RFL6mTGHUGsfhU-x5DUFQ2?nvep=&hmac=&emc
 i=dce6295d-4917-f111-a69a-000d3a1f0a97&emdi=ea000000-0000-0000-0000-000000
 000001&ceid=
X-SOURCE:Solutions Journalism Network
END:VEVENT
